nunn library NEWS -- history of user-visible changes.
Author - Antonino Calderone - <acaldmail@gmail.com> - (c) 2015, 2016

Please send nunn bug reports to <acaldmail@gmail.com>.

Jun 28, 2026
* Added GRU, rnn_adding benchmark, and RNN training scripts

New: Gru (nu_gru.h / nu_gru.cc) — Gated Recurrent Unit with truncated BPTT
- Architecture: reset gate r_t, update gate z_t, candidate g_t; no cell state
- ~25% fewer parameters than an equal-size LSTM
- Input weights stacked [r;z;h] (_W [3·nh×ni]); single GEMV for r and z gates
- Separate recurrent weight _Uh applied to r_t⊙h_{t-1} for the candidate
- BPTT backward: three paths to dh_prev (direct, through candidate, through gates)
- Same public API as VanillaRnn and Lstm; drop-in swap via --gru flag in examples
- 14 unit tests: construction, reset, step, softmax, BPTT, convergence (identity/echo/binary)

New example: rnn_adding — the "adding problem" selective-memory benchmark
- Input: sequences of (value, marker) pairs; one marker in each half
- Target: cumulative sum of marked values (many-to-many MSE formulation)
- Trains VanillaRnn, GRU, and LSTM on identical datasets and prints a comparison
- Positional args: [seq_len=20] [hidden=32] [epochs=500] [lr=0.005]

Updated examples: rnn_sine and rnn_char now support --gru / --lstm / (default VanillaRnn)

New scripts: scripts/rnn/ — ready-made run-and-compare scripts
- powershell/: run_sine.ps1, run_char.ps1, run_adding.ps1, run_all.ps1
- bash/:       run_sine.sh,  run_char.sh,  run_adding.sh,  run_all.sh
- -Quick / --quick flag for fast smoke-tests
- -Model / --model flag to select one or all architectures
- Comparison table printed when multiple models are evaluated

Jun 27, 2026
* Added VanillaRnn and LSTM recurrent neural networks

New: VanillaRnn (nu_rnn.h) — Elman-style RNN with truncated BPTT
- Architecture: h_t = tanh(Wx·x_t + Wh·h_{t-1} + b_h), y_t = f_out(Wy·h_t + b_y)
- Linear output (MSE) and Softmax output (cross-entropy) modes
- Truncated BPTT with per-element gradient clipping
- Xavier normal weight initialisation; resetState() / step() / bptt() / reshuffleWeights()
- 14 unit tests covering construction, step, BPTT, convergence (identity, echo, binary sequence)

New: Lstm (nu_lstm.h) — LSTM with truncated BPTT
- 4-gate architecture (input, forget, output, cell candidate)
- Gate weights stacked [i;f;o;g] for a single GEMV per step
- Forget-gate bias initialised to 1 (standard trick to aid early gradient flow)
- Same public API as VanillaRnn; drop-in swap via --lstm flag in examples
- 14 unit tests (same coverage as VanillaRnn tests)

New examples:
- rnn_sine: predict sin(t+1) from sin(t); teacher-forcing training then autoregressive
  inference; supports --lstm, positional args for epochs/hidden/lr
- rnn_char: character-level language model on embedded English corpus (~28-char vocab);
  temperature-scaled sampling for text generation; supports --lstm

Scripts:
- scripts/mnist/ reorganised into powershell/ and bash/ subdirectories
- Bash equivalents added for all 7 training configs and run_all

Bug fixes (committed separately):
- Perceptron backPropagate(): MSE gradient now includes sigmoid derivative
  delta = (t-y)*y*(1-y); CE gradient unchanged (delta = t-y)
- Perceptron: momentum support added (matches MlpMatrixNN pattern)
- Perceptron: save/load/JSON round-trip preserves momentum and cost function
- NNTrainer::runTraining(): early stopping now checks epoch-average cost
  (textbook convention) instead of stopping on any single-sample threshold
- NNTrainer::end(): fixed iterator off-by-one (_epochs+1 corrected to _epochs)
- run_all.ps1: replaced UTF-8 em-dash with ASCII -- to fix PS 5.1 parse error

Jun 27, 2026
* Released nunn library 2.1

Core:
- CostFunction enum moved to nu_costfuncs.h (shared between MlpNN and MlpMatrixNN)
- CrossEntropy+Sigmoid constraint enforced at construction time in both MlpNN and
  MlpMatrixNN via InvalidCostFunctionCombinationException
- CE+Sigmoid gradient: delta = t - a (sigmoid derivative cancels, correct formula)

New: MlpMatrixNN — Eigen 3.4.0 backed matrix MLP
- Weights stored as Eigen::MatrixXd [out x in] per layer
- Forward pass via GEMV (single sample) and GEMM (mini-batch via trainBatch)
- Same per-layer activation and CE+Sigmoid constraint as MlpNN
- 128 unit tests covering API, XOR convergence, and mini-batch SGD

New: mnist_test --matrix / --batch flags
- --matrix / -M selects MlpMatrixNN instead of MlpNN
- --batch N / -b N enables mini-batch SGD (default 1 = online SGD)
- Epoch time (ms) and throughput (samples/s) reported each epoch

Build:
- Eigen 3.4.0 fetched via CMake FetchContent (header-only, no extra install)
- mnist helper library changed from SHARED to STATIC (no runtime DLL needed)
- GoogleTest fetched via FetchContent; 128 tests registered with CTest

Scripts (scripts/mnist/):
- All training scripts default to --matrix --batch 32 (MlpMatrixNN)
- -NoMatrix switch restores classic MlpNN path
- run_all.ps1 shows Backend and Throughput columns in results table

Bug fixes (backported from ongoing work):
- Vector(const double*, size_t): fixed byte-count vs element-count copy
- SoftmaxPolicy: fixed end-iterator dereference and zero/negative temperature
- EGreedyPolicy: clamped random action index to valid range
- Sarsa::learn(): move counter was incremented twice per step
- NNTrainer::runTraining(): sample index now advances without progress callback
- QLearn::updateQ(): guard against states with no valid actions
- MlpNN/Perceptron save(): doubles written at full precision

